''[[The Games Machine]]'' said that it was "an excellent two-player head-to-head combat game", and calling it "very fast, very playable, and, more often than not, very tense".<ref name=":0" />

''[[Zzap!64|ZZap!64]]'' called the game "fun" despite being "oversimplified", and saying it was a "good game in its own right" despite the fact that fans of the original might be disappointed.<ref name=ZzapRef>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/zzap64-magazine-030/ZZap_64_Issue_030_1987_Oct#page/n97/mode/2up|title=ZZap!64 Magazine Issue 030|website=archive.org|date=October 1987 |access-date=2017-07-28}}</ref>

''[[Computer and Video Games]]'' said "the fiddly controls are kept to a bare minimum".<ref name=CVGRev>{{Cite web|magazine=Computer and Video Games|publisher=[[EMAP]]|issn=0261-3697|issue=72|url=https://archive.org/stream/computer-video-games-magazine-072/CVG072_Oct_1987#page/n27/mode/2up|title=Ace II|access-date=2017-07-28}}</ref>

